“This is how we make a living. There are more than 500 people using the Uber and Bolt service to make a living. If they want us to stop operating, how are we going to live?” 
YoTaxi denied they were “using force” but said they would allow law enforcement to deal with illegal operators. 
“If vehicles are being used for public transport and making money out of it, they must have permits to operate,” said a member.

Provincial spokesperson Brigadier Jay Naicker said about 150 e-hailing drivers blocked the road. Police were forced to use stun grenades. “Three vehicles were impounded,” he said.
The Mercury